No. 155,

Misc.

In re Disbarment of Quimby.

Charles H. Quimby III, Esquire, of Washington, D. C., having resigned as a member of the Bar of this Court, it is ordered that his name be stricken from the roll of attorneys admitted to practice. [For earlier orders herein, see 387 U. S. 927, 389 U. S. 1012.]
